{
  "texts": [
    ", and L t = KL(q(x t-1 |x t, x 0)||p θ (x t-1 |x t)).",
    "KL represents the KL-divergence of two distributions.",
    "Furthermore, since q(x t-1 |x t, x 0) follows a normal distribution, we can calculate the closed form of KL-divergence.",
    "As proposed in DDPM (Ho et al. 2020), the optimization of the function L vlb can be achieved by minimizing the deviation between the model's true noise and approximate noise at random time steps in the trajectory:",
    "where E is the expected value calculation, ϵ θ (x t, t) is predict noise in step t by neural network, x 0 is the initial data."
  ]
}